

Photo 1: Food Court Counter

Description:
This photograph shows the food court service area at VIT University. It contains multiple food counters, menu boards, billing systems, and customer service desks where students place food orders.

Source of Photography:
Primary source – Photograph captured by the author using the GPS Map Camera application.

Place:
Food Court, VIT University, Vellore, Tamil Nadu, India.

Reasons Why the Design is Bad:

The menu boards contain too much information, making them difficult to read quickly.

The font size is small, reducing visibility from a distance.

Exposed electrical wires below the menu boards create a cluttered and unprofessional appearance.

There is no clear indication of customer queues or service flow.


Suggested Improvements:

Replace static menu boards with digital displays.

Increase font size and improve color contrast.

Hide electrical cables using proper cable management.

Add queue management barriers and clear directional signage.



